Let us define the following data transformations

frequencies <- 
Spec$Frequency %>% 
  str_replace("q", "3") %>% 
  str_replace("m", "1") %>% 
  as.numeric()

lin <- function(z, freq) z

chg <- function(z, freq) {
  z - lag(z, freq)
}

ch1 <- function(z, freq) {
  chg(z, 12)
}

pch <- function(z, freq) {
  100 * ( z / lag(z, freq) - 1 )
}

pc1 <- function(z, freq) {
  pch(z, 12)
}

pca <- function(z, freq) {
  y <- z / lag(z, freq)
  100 * ( y ** (freq / 12) - 1 )
}

He filters his columns via the Model column in Specs. We deliberatly are not filtering because I want to see where it all goes wrong.

X %>% 
  mutate_at(vars(-Date), ~ (.x - mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE))/ sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE))

We will deal with NAs in the following way:

  • We will check if rows have more than 80% of their columns with NAs.
  • We will remove rows from the beginning until we reach the first row that has at least 80% of columns filled. Then we stop.
  • We will remove rows from the ending until we reach the first row that has at least 80% of columns filled. Then we stop.
condition <- 
X %>% 
  select(-Date) %>% 
  (function(x) rowSums(is.na(x)) > ncol(X) * 0.8) %>% 
  cumsum() 

pmap(list(condition, 1:nrow(X), nrow(X):1),
    ~ !(..1 == ..2 | ..1 == ..3)
) %>% unlist()
